50|$|The <b>Assizes</b> <b>of</b> Capua {{were the}} first of three great {{legislative}} acts of the kingdom of Sicily of Frederick II of Sicily, Holy Roman Emperor. They {{were the first}}, promulgated at Capua in 1220, before the <b>Assizes</b> <b>of</b> Messina on 1221 and the Constitutions of Melfi of 1231.|$|R
